Since the colors in the legend are in different order

let's try separating out into different facets - see Chapter 1 (cross-ref needed)
color to fill
geom_area \index{ggplot2!geom\_area} \index{ggplot2!facet\_wrap}

\index{area chart}



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(
  data = plot_data,
  mapping = aes(x = year, y = museums, fill = deprivation)
) +
  geom_area() +
  facet_wrap(~deprivation, nrow = 2)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![An area chart of total number of museums open per year for each level of deprivation, with the each deprivation level in a different facet.](uk-museums_files/figure-pdf/fig-museums-basic-plot-2-1.pdf){#fig-museums-basic-plot-2 fig-pos='H'}
:::
